<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-37-0245 </DOCNO><TEXT>The advantages of energy from natural gas esp. for the glass industryare described. The development of natural gas consumption in West Germanyis compared to that of other energies, the consumption is indicated perbranch of industry. The main issue here is the distribution of varioussources of energy in the glass industry. The advantages of natural gasin terms of safety of supplies, environmental benefits and rational utilizationare emphasized. (HLN).</TEXT></DOC>